  "title": "Project Manager (FTC) - Up to $3.6k/month + AWS",
  "description": "<p><strong>Working Location: CBD Area</strong><br /><strong>Monthly Salary: Up to $3.6k/month </strong><br /><strong>Working Hours: 5-day work week </strong><br /></p><p><strong>Job Purpose: </strong><br />The Project Manager (Coordinator) will be responsible for coordinating and managing promotional activities aimed at expanding the market presence of Japanese food and agricultural products in Singapore. The role involves close collaboration with both internal stakeholders and external partners. <strong>This is a fixed-term contract with a tentative start date in April 2026 for a period of 1 year</strong>. <br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities: </strong></p><ul><li>Plan, coordinate, and support promotional activities to expand the market for Japanese food products in Singapore.</li><li>Conduct market research related to promotional initiatives.</li><li>Manage external vendors and service providers involved in marketing and event execution.</li><li>Coordinate with event organisers, local companies, contractors, and internal teams.</li><li>Build and maintain networks with food industry stakeholders, influencers, and related partners.</li><li>Manage and update social media content related to promotional activities.</li><li>Handle internal administrative procedures, including approvals and expense processing.</li><li><strong>Prepare internal documents and reports in</strong> <strong>Japanese</strong>.</li><li>Perform other administrative and operational tasks as required.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>At least a Diploma/Associate Degree or Bachelor's Degree in a related field. </li></ul><p><u><em><strong>(Must Have)</strong></em></u></p><ul><li>Proficiency in English at a business or near-native level.</li><li>Proficiency in Japanese equivalent to JLPT N1 level or higher as needed to converse and write reports in Japanese for stakeholders. </li><li>Strong interest in Japanese food and Japanese culture.</li><li>Proficiency in PC applications (Excel, Word, PowerPoint) and online communication tools (e.g. Zoom, Microsoft Teams)</li></ul><p><u><em><strong>(Good to Have)</strong></em></u></p><ul><li>Prior experience in marketing or related roles.</li><li>Ability to manage schedules and follow internal procedures accurately and consistently.</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to communicate effectively with diverse stakeholders.</li></ul><p><br />Nextbeat Singapore Pte. Ltd.<br />EA License Number: 22C1267<br />EA Personnel No: R22110252</p>",
